Pre-Game Insights: Guinea need at least a point to seal their berth in the knockout stage but can also qualify for the next stage as one of the best-ranked third-placed teams from the group stage depending on other results.
Senegal have the best attacking record in the group stage of the competition, scoring three goals apiece in two games.
Captain Naby Keïta made an appearance from the bench after recovering from a thigh injury and is expected to start here.
Striker Serhou Guirassy is dealing with a hamstring issue and is not in contention to start here.
Moussa Niakhaté suffered an injury in the campaign opener while Abdallah Sima was injured in training last week. Sima has left the camp while Niakhaté's involvement here is in doubt.
